							"authorNames": "Mitra Nasri (Eindhoven University of Technology), Jeroen Voeten (Eindhoven University of Technology)",
							"abstract": "This paper explores the design and verification of real-time cyber-physical systems transitioning from embedded platforms to the cloud. It covers opportunities, potential use cases, and challenges associated with the timing predictability of cloud-enabled real-time systems. The conclusion outlines future research directions to address these challenges.",
							"searchText": "2024 IEEE Workshop on Design Automation for CPS and IoT (DESTION) DESTION 2024 A Position Paper on Transforming Embedded Real-Time Systems to the Cloud: Challenges and New Research Directions 1711098840383 10.1109/DESTION62938.2024.00012 Mitra Nasri Eindhoven University of Technology m.nasri@tue.nl Jeroen Voeten Eindhoven University of Technology j.p.m.voeten@tue.nl real-time systems cloud design cycle This paper explores the design and verification of real-time cyber-physical systems transitioning from embedded platforms to the cloud. It covers opportunities, potential use cases, and challenges associated with the timing predictability of cloud-enabled real-time systems. The conclusion outlines future research directions to address these challenges.",
