							"abstract": "We propose to demonstrate a novel underground potato root tuber sensing framework via a wireless network. We build a data acquisition system for capturing the ground truth of the tuber shape and the received signal strength (RSS) measurements on multiple channels of the wireless network. Then we design a two-module neural network to reconstruct the cross-section images of potato tubers. Our initial experimental results show that the reconstructed images can be used to predict the size of various potato tubers buried underground with high accuracy. We will demonstrate real-time performance of our prototype.",
