							"abstract": "The demand for fully on-device health monitoring is huge and urgent. However, deploying Large Foundation Models conventionally relies on cloud-based computing services, which poses privacy concerns. Driven by the belief of delivering personalised healthcare to family members, this study presents the development of an innovative on-device machine learning system, CaringFM. This family caring system utilizes privacy-protecting sensors and an edge-deployed Foundation Model(FM) to offer a convenient and low-cost solution for chronic disease prediction and health condition monitoring at home. In particular, CaringFM provides general health suggestions and personalized medical information while ensuring high privacy by processing and preserving all data locally.",
							"searchText": "2024 23rd ACM/IEEE International Conference on Information Processing in Sensor Networks (IPSN) IPSN 2024 Demo Abstract: CaringFM: An Interactive In-Home Healthcare System Empowered by Large Foundation Models 1711860438088 10.1109/IPSN61024.2024.00028 Haiyang Wu The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR n/a Kaiwei Liu The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR n/a Siyang Jiang The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR n/a Zhihe Zhao The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR n/a Zhenyu Yan The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR n/a Guoliang Xing The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Hong Kong SAR glxing@cuhk.edu.hk Large Foundation Model Human Activity Recognition The demand for fully on-device health monitoring is huge and urgent. However, deploying Large Foundation Models conventionally relies on cloud-based computing services, which poses privacy concerns. Driven by the belief of delivering personalised healthcare to family members, this study presents the development of an innovative on-device machine learning system, CaringFM. This family caring system utilizes privacy-protecting sensors and an edge-deployed Foundation Model(FM) to offer a convenient and low-cost solution for chronic disease prediction and health condition monitoring at home. In particular, CaringFM provides general health suggestions and personalized medical information while ensuring high privacy by processing and preserving all data locally.",
