							"type": "authorPaper",
							"text": "Demo Abstract: Range-SLAM: UWB Based Realtime Indoor Location and Mapping",
							"articleLocation": "pdfs/IPSN2024-5oOtDbD5wNMG5iVx5ZwNYy/620100a259/620100a259.pdf",
							"extraLocations": [],
							"authorNames": "Yi Liu (Shandong University, China), Zhuozhu Jian (Tsinghua University, China), Junbo Tan (Tsinghua University, China), Lunfei Liang (Harbin Institute of Technology, China), Houde Liu (Tsinghua University, China), Xinlei Chen (Tsinghua University, China; Pengcheng Laboratory; RISC-V International Open Source Laboratory)",
							"abstract": "Simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) systems frequently employ LiDAR and cameras as essential sensing components. However, these sensors are proved to be unreliable in environments with poor visibility or reflective surfaces. And UWB (Ultra Wide Band) sensor with a longer wavelength shows better potential to achieve perception tasks. However, since UWB sensors can only obtain distance information from the anchors, it is difficult to densely construct the geometric structure of the environment. In this paper, We propose Range-SLAM, a method based on received signal strength indicator (RSSI) recognition and binary filtering to complete the mapping task and enhance positioning based on the map, and only require UWB as external perception sensor. Real-world experiments are conducted and prove the effectiveness, real-time performance and robustness of the Range-SLAM algorithm.",
							"searchText": "2024 23rd ACM/IEEE International Conference on Information Processing in Sensor Networks (IPSN) IPSN 2024 Demo Abstract: Range-SLAM: UWB Based Realtime Indoor Location and Mapping 1712218374544 10.1109/IPSN61024.2024.00030 Yi Liu Shandong University, China n/a Zhuozhu Jian Tsinghua University, China n/a Junbo Tan Tsinghua University, China n/a Lunfei Liang Harbin Institute of Technology, China n/a Houde Liu Tsinghua University, China n/a Xinlei Chen Tsinghua University, China; Pengcheng Laboratory; RISC-V International Open Source Laboratory n/a Simultaneous localization and mapping RSSI UWB Simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) systems frequently employ LiDAR and cameras as essential sensing components. However, these sensors are proved to be unreliable in environments with poor visibility or reflective surfaces. And UWB (Ultra Wide Band) sensor with a longer wavelength shows better potential to achieve perception tasks. However, since UWB sensors can only obtain distance information from the anchors, it is difficult to densely construct the geometric structure of the environment. In this paper, We propose Range-SLAM, a method based on received signal strength indicator (RSSI) recognition and binary filtering to complete the mapping task and enhance positioning based on the map, and only require UWB as external perception sensor. Real-world experiments are conducted and prove the effectiveness, real-time performance and robustness of the Range-SLAM algorithm.",
