							"authorNames": "Laura Tileutay (Ajou University, South Korea), Jiwoong Park (Ajou University, South Korea), Young-Bae Ko (Ajou University, South Korea)",
							"abstract": "Ultra-wideband technology has the potential to provide precise real-world localization. However, due to Non-Line-of-Sight propagation, the transmitted packet can be incomplete or lost during the ranging, which may lead to communication failure. To minimize this, we propose the scheduled signal reception technique. The proposed approach is tested in a real-world environment with Qorvo DWM3001C modules. The experimental results verify its efficiency, offering a practical solution for UWB-based localization, particularly in dynamic circumstances.",
							"searchText": "2024 23rd ACM/IEEE International Conference on Information Processing in Sensor Networks (IPSN) IPSN 2024 Poster Abstract: UWB Ranging with Scheduled Broken Packet Reception 1711938096148 10.1109/IPSN61024.2024.00051 Laura Tileutay Ajou University, South Korea tileutaylaura@ajou.ac.kr Jiwoong Park Ajou University, South Korea z7080z@ajou.ac.kr Young-Bae Ko Ajou University, South Korea youngko@ajou.ac.kr Localization Ultra-Wideband Preamble detection Ultra-wideband technology has the potential to provide precise real-world localization. However, due to Non-Line-of-Sight propagation, the transmitted packet can be incomplete or lost during the ranging, which may lead to communication failure. To minimize this, we propose the scheduled signal reception technique. The proposed approach is tested in a real-world environment with Qorvo DWM3001C modules. The experimental results verify its efficiency, offering a practical solution for UWB-based localization, particularly in dynamic circumstances.",
