							"abstract": "This poster introduces SynMotion, a novel mmWave-based human motion sensing system addressing the scarcity of training datasets. By synthesizing mmWave signals using existing vision-based human motion datasets, this system overcomes the challenge of collecting and labeling mmWave data, facilitating wider adoption of mmWave technology for applications like activity recognition, skeleton tracking and radar placement recommendation.",
							"searchText": "2024 23rd ACM/IEEE International Conference on Information Processing in Sensor Networks (IPSN) IPSN 2024 Poster Abstract: Enhancing Human Motion Sensing with Synthesized Millimeter-Waves 1712058186045 10.1109/IPSN61024.2024.00054 Xiaotong Zhang City University of Hong Kong, China; Southern University of Science and Technology, China n/a Kun Wang City University of Hong Kong, China n/a Zhenjiang Li City University of Hong Kong, China n/a Jin Zhang Southern University of Science and Technology, China; Peng Cheng Laboratory, China n/a Human Motion Sensing, MillimeterWave, Body Skeleton Tracking, Activity Recognition This poster introduces SynMotion, a novel mmWave-based human motion sensing system addressing the scarcity of training datasets. By synthesizing mmWave signals using existing vision-based human motion datasets, this system overcomes the challenge of collecting and labeling mmWave data, facilitating wider adoption of mmWave technology for applications like activity recognition, skeleton tracking and radar placement recommendation.",
